However, what I really expect is that when I enter the zone, I will find a gnome standing inside the outpost there.  The encounter will go something like this:<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze regards you indifferently.<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;Hail, Hafite Snizznoze.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze says, &quot;Hail, Rrraowl.  What a lovely place this is, though I am saddened by the ravages of [war] that I see.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;What war?&quot;<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze says, &quot;Alas, I fear the owlbears, sonic wolves and grimlings may never learn to live in peace.  Nevertheless, the gods see fit to keep them all here, [living together] in the same land.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;They are not actually living together.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze says, &quot;What???  Can it be that [two of the races have been eliminated] already?&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;Yep, two of the races have been elliminated already.&quot;<br>
<br>
You say, &quot;Two of the races have been eliminated.&quot;<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze begins to cast a spell.<br>
<br>
Hafite Snizznoze says, &quot;Good heavens, you are right.  By the power of the gods (that you Vah Shir do not follow), I cleanse the zone of violence and despair!&quot;<br>
<br>
Hollowshade Moor has been reset.<br>
